k and the zombie sessions. The three main ones are the QLHV progress monitor, the DTLX progress monitor, and the Telegram group session for QLHV. I need to calculate how long each has been running based on their start times and the current timestamp. Calculating the elapsed time for the cron:6f3323ef session, which shows about 6 hours 47 minutes of runtime, though the task description is cut off mid-word.\\n\\nThe Telegram group session has been running for approximately 1 hour 55 minutes. I've identified the target session key for sending the report and need to format it properly before delivery.\\n\\nThe session appears to still be active with a running status, so I can proceed with sending the message directly to the Telegram group session using the appropriate session identifier.\\n\\nNow I'm composing the status report with all the required session information included.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"I can see the active sessions clearly. The Lead's direct session (`telegram:direct:6053576134`) is currently **done** — but the most recent message it received was my own status report from this cron at 14:45 UTC. Let me compile and send.\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_0p7dmdfe7uct_1\",\n              \"name\": \"sessions_send\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n                \"message\": \"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 14:57 UTC 14 Apr\\n\\nActive sessions: 3\\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV): running — 5-min progress monitoring (QLHV ecosystem) — ~15m\\n• cron:6f3323ef (5p DTLX): running — 5-min progress monitoring (DTLX ecosystem) — ~6h 47m\\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 (QLHV group): running — QLHV ecosystem session — ~1h 56m\\n\\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\\n• Blockers: ⚠️ 2 zombie cron sessions lingering (pre-existing, no failures)\\n• No new failures, no blockers.\\n\\n— Orbis 🌐\",\n                \"timeoutSeconds\": 25\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 28707,\n            \"output\": 710,\n            \"totalTokens\": 43563,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13849,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 297,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776178734120,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d892fab381b432ca2fec9f0656740\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"220152bb\",\n            \"seq\": 4\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The sessions_send timed out again. This is a known transient gateway issue. The report is ready. Let me just output it as plain text here for the cron delivery mechanism to handle.\\n\\nActually, looking at the instructions: \\\"Send the report to Lead directly via sessions_send to sessionKey: agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\\\" - the sessions_send already timed out. I should just output the plain text report so it can be delivered somehow. But the cron is an isolated agentTurn, so the plain text reply here IS the delivery mechanism.\\n\\nLet me output the report as plain text.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Gateway timed out — transient. Here's the report as plain text (deliverable):\\n\\n---\\n\\n🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 14:57 UTC 14 Apr\\n\\nActive sessions: 3\\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV): running — 5-min progress monitoring (QLHV ecosystem) — ~15m\\n• cron:6f3323ef (5p D